text.text: Poleramma! Goddess Poleramma is a Pre Vedic deity goddess, who is predominantly worshipped in the state of Andhra Pradesh. Poleramma is a local form of Sakti in Andhra pradesh. She is worshipped as Grama devata, Goddess who protects the village. Very powerful as per the rural people of Andhra Pradesh. Mother Poleramma is worshipped as a village guardian goddess to protect the village. The shrine is usually kept outside the village
